Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto one side of a large #baking tray{}, cut-side up.

Spread over half the garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread. Set aside for now.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and fry until softened, ~{4-5%mins}. Meanwhile, tear half the @chorizo slices{50%grams} into small pieces.

Once the onion has softened, add the torn chorizo and remaining garlic to the pan. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%mins}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high. Drain and tear the @mozzarella{1%ball}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the sauce a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir the cooked pasta and half the torn mozzarella into the sauce until the cheese has melted. Taste and season with salt and @pepper{}.

Transfer the pasta and sauce to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Top the pasta with the remaining mozzarella pieces, then lay the remaining chorizo slices on top.

Pop your ovenproof dish onto the baking tray alongside the garlic ciabatta. Grill until the ciabatta is golden and the pasta is bubbling, ~{5-6%mins}.

> Grill the ciabatta and pasta separately if you run out of space.

When the garlic ciabatta is ready, cut in half diagonally.

Share the pizza inspired pasta bake between your #serving bowls{}.

Serve the garlic ciabatta alongside. Enjoy!